	<xhtml:h1>Example Birthday Book Z specification</xhtml:h1>
	(Note how we can intersperse text and XML constructs from other namespaces with the Z constructs).
	
	<Sect>
		<Name>Specification</Name>
		
		First we declare some <xhtml:em>given types</xhtml:em>.
		<GivenPara>
			<DeclName>
				<Word>NAME</Word>
			</DeclName>
			<DeclName>
				<Word>DATE</Word>
			</DeclName>
		</GivenPara>
		
		Here is an example of an unknown paragraph that is not Z-related
		(it could be some Z extension), so is ignored by standard Z tools.
		<Foo:SomethingUnknown>x := x + 1</Foo:SomethingUnknown>
		
		This huge thing is just the state schema of the Birthday Book.  (I'm not sure which kind of function birthday is).
		<xhtml:pre>
			BirthdayBook = [known: P NAME; birthday : NAME -?-> DATE | known = dom birthday ]
		</xhtml:pre>
